dev work:
1. clean up lexer
2. add support for bold and italics(?)
3. rework parser for simplicity; we don't need this whole recursive nonsense
4. create a clean "slide" data structure.


Work:
1. auto scaling mode (1 font, no formatting) just works
    - will strip out markers and just draw text/images
2. pretty mode: actually care about parsing headers etc, but have to manually set font sizes


Arch:
lexer -> parser -> []slide -> draw (regular or pretty) -> render

the parser produces a list of slides
a list of slides is just a list of typed lines
- line types: comment, header, subheader, plain, etc

In regular mode, we just draw all the text, centered and scaled
Pretty mode adds dedicated font sizes and colors to the different line types

